@wesleybrad060 @apyx_fi @strata_markets @saturn_credit @saylor @Strategy Let's break it down for you.

Every apxUSD is overcollateralized by $STRC. But dividends are only emitted to a smaller subset of staked apxUSD (i.e. apyUSD), which is why apyUSD yield is typically higher than $STRC's dividend rate.

Pendle is a yield infra that splits these

@apyx_fi Royco splits apyUSD into 2 vaults with different risk exposure.

Senior capital (srRoyAPYUSD) earns yield with a cushion beneath it.

Junior capital (jrRoyAPYUSD) provides that cushion, and gets paid more for the risks it takes up.
